definition.value: An omega-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 2-benzylsuccinic acid.
A fatty acid ester obtained by the formal condensation of hydroxy group of benzyl alcohol with the carboxy group of 3-hydroxy-2-methylbutanoic acid.
Any isoquinoline alkaloid based on a benzylisoquinoline skeleton.
